terrapeer.vui.j3dui.feedback.elements
Class TextureCone

java.lang.Object
  javax.media.j3d.SceneGraphObject
      javax.media.j3d.Node
          javax.media.j3d.Group
              terrapeer.vui.j3dui.feedback.elements.TextureShape
                  terrapeer.vui.j3dui.feedback.elements.TextureCone
public class TextureCone
extends TextureShape

Creates a conical texture shape (see TextureShape).

The axis of the cone is the Y axis. The base is located at zero along the Y axis. The apex is located at a specified height along the +Y axis. The side towards +Y is the "top"

the texture is projected "down" onto the cone. The center of the texture corresponds to the peak of the cone. The edge of the cone corresponds to a circle tangent to the sides of the texture image. The texture +X axis is parallel to the cone +X axis. Top and bottom side textures will match. If the texture can not be loaded it is ignored with a warning.

See Also:
TextureShape

Parameters:

radius - Radius of the cone base.
height - Height of the cone from base to peak.
